{
  "stem": "26699.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the generation of my parents, they were non-religious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] celebrating, keeping the big-- the high holy days, Pesach, Yom Kippur, Rosh Hashanah, the Shabbat lighting candles, but this was about all.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the death trains were related to the totality of events, to the pogrom, which took place in Iasi, so cannot be separated.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So if it's going to discuss the death trains, we have to discuss the whole event of the pogrom of Iasi.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And let's talk about this subject, that I think is the focal point of my memories.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] In the month of June 1941, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] when Romania is in full summer, it's very hot, it's pleasant weather, in good times-- what my father used to call normal times-- people go to spas, holidays.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The German army invaded Romania.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I cannot call a proper invasion, because Romania became an ally of Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It is disputable.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some people say that Romania was forced to become an ally, but in any case, with the approval of the government, a very large German army came into Romania.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Some of them, probably, from the occupied Poland, which was conquered in 1938.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we're talking three years after this event.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the German army was at its peak.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were preparing themselves with the Romanian army, and you could have felt in this town movement of large numbers of German soldiers and Romanian soldiers, like preparing for something that is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was a child, so I saw soldiers, they looked great to me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Soldiers, particularly the German soldiers, very well-dressed and neat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Romanian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- but I knew that my parents were very worried about all this.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
